The Rabbit Federal Reserve is a collection of 24000 unique NFTs — unique digital arts living on the Ethereum blockchain. 
1000 NFTs are created every year.
From 2023-01-22 to 2024-02-09, the Fed starts to sell NFTs at 0.05 eth, and it buys back all listed NFTs at 0.1 eth on 2024-02-10.
From 2024-02-10 to 2025-01-28, the Fed starts to sell NFTs at 0.1 eth, and it buys back all listed NFTs at 0.2 eth on 2025-01-29.
From 2025-01-29 to 2026-02-16, the Fed starts to sell NFTs at 0.2 eth, and it buys back all listed NFTs at 0.4 eth on 2026-02-17.
From 2026-02-17 to 2027-02-05, the Fed starts to sell NFTs at 0.4 eth, and it buys back all listed NFTs at 0.8 eth on 2027-02-06.
…
From 2034-02-19 to 2035-02-07, the Fed starts to sell NFTs at 204.8 eth, and it buys back all listed NFTs at 409.6 eth on 2035-02-08.
